<h2 class="title">Privacy Policy (Draft)</h2>
<p><strong>Effective date:</strong> June 13, 2026</p>
<p>This draft policy explains how Amherst Community Band ("ACB," "we," "our," or "us") handles information collected through this website.</p>

<h3 class="title is-4">Information We Collect</h3>
<p>We may collect information that you provide directly in the Contact popup form, including your name, email address, and message content.</p>

<h3 class="title is-4">How We Use Information</h3>
<p>We use submitted information to respond to inquiries, provide requested information, and communicate about Amherst Community Band activities.</p>

<h3 class="title is-4">Third-Party Services and Embedded Content</h3>
<p>This site may use third-party services and embeds, including Formspree (contact form processing), YouTube (video embeds), Google Maps links, and Google Calendar embeds. These services may collect information according to their own privacy policies.</p>

<h3 class="title is-4">Cookies and Analytics</h3>
<p>This site does not currently run a separate analytics platform controlled by ACB. Embedded third-party services may set cookies or similar technologies.</p>

<h3 class="title is-4">Data Sharing</h3>
<p>We do not sell personal information. We share information only as needed with service providers that operate site features (for example, contact form processing).</p>

<h3 class="title is-4">Data Retention</h3>
<p>Contact submissions are retained for as long as reasonably needed to respond and maintain communication records, unless a longer period is required by law.</p>

<h3 class="title is-4">Your Choices</h3>
<p>You may choose not to submit contact information. If you contact us and want your message deleted, request removal using the contact information below.</p>

<h3 class="title is-4">Contact</h3>
<p>For privacy questions or requests, please use the site contact channel shown in the footer (Webmaster link) or the Contact popup.</p>

<h3 class="title is-4">Policy Updates</h3>
<p>We may update this policy from time to time. The effective date at the top will reflect the latest revision.</p>